  "text": "Some evidence exists that the angular momentum of the Solar wind is, at least instantaneously, not perfectly aligned along the spin axis [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Thus, even if the star-formation process resulted in a perfectly-aligned system of planetary orbits around an aligned stellar equator, stochasticity in the stellar wind may in principle drive a deviation from this aligned architecture over its subsequent evolution.",
